@dimatosj You aren’t supposed to transport it in an elevator. Spills are really dangerous b/c of asphyxiation.
@dimatosj And never put it in a sealed container. It expands 16ish:1, so N2 bombs in 2L bottles are super dangerous.
@dimatosj And beware enclosed spaces, elevators and stairwells in particular. N2 is heavier than air, so it will fill bottom of long shafts.
@dimatosj The TLDR is wear eye protection and closed toed shoes. Don’t let it get trapped between clothes and skin. Treat like fryer oil.
